      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "SWEET ON LEXY (5) made an impressive switch to Queensland when he drew on the back row but worked his way to the front before cruising home by 17m. Drops to a distance where he has won three of five attempts and a front row draw should see him hard to stop. PATH TO GREATNESS (7) resumes from a spell of nine weeks after closing off last campaign with three straight wins at this venue. Has to contend with a very wide draw but he is talented and races well when fresh so expect a bright start to the campaign. MEGS BOY NZ (10) tackles a couple of handy rivals tonight and the draw looks tricky but he is very hard to knock after putting five wins together, two of them from this row. The inside draw could see last-start placegetter CHARGE AHEAD (1) in the finish again.",
